@chapter Motivation for writing it-edit


@quotation

They are 2 sort of programmers in their habits of writing programs:


@itemize *

@item 
They which use an IDE with full integrated functionalities.

@item 
They which use an text editor to write their programs and a terminal to compile, debug or launch them and some other tools separately.
@end itemize

Because i'am an programmer from the second category and because i remark that i often use an additional other tools.

I decide to write my own text editor program which provide me all the functionalities that i need to get a development environment fully adapt to my requirement.

Which consist of a terminal integrated text-editor with which you can access all you require directly from the editor: documentation, GUI applications, ...
@end quotation

@node it-edit presentation,Files,Motivation for writing it-edit,Top
@anchor{it-edit it-edit-presentation}@anchor{4}
@chapter it-edit presentation


@quotation

@strong{it-edit} provide a text editor with @code{syntax highlight}, @code{line numbering} and with the basics text editing functionalities:


@itemize *

@item 
Cut, Copy and Paste.

@item 
Duplicate a line or the selected text.

@item 
Undo/Redo functionalities.

@item 
Search and replace functionalities.

@item 
Jump to the given line number.

@item 
Enable | Disable the use of tabs.
@end itemize

And an files managing interface for:


@itemize *

@item 
Open a new empty file.

@item 
Open the file you want.

@item 
Open an recent file.

@item 
Save the editor content.

@item 
Save the editor content as the filename you want.

@item 
Save all open files.

@item 
Reload file.

@item 
File informations.
@end itemize

@strong{it-edit} provide @strong{terminals in the same window as the editor}, as a sidebar, which can easily @strong{shown}, @strong{hidden} and @strong{resized}.

You can @strong{add} and @strong{remove} as many terminals as you want to the sidebar...

@strong{it-edit} provide a @strong{big terminal} occupying the full interface, @strong{dividable} into @strong{4 resizable terminals}, to which you can @strong{easy toggle} from the main window.

For executing commands like compilation, debugging, and so soon directly from the editor.


@display
@w{ }
@end display



I intend to implement an @code{manpages reading interface}, in an @strong{toplevel terminal window} (so it can be @strong{resize}, @strong{minimize}, @strong{maximize} and @strong{closed}),

@quotation

but i remark by implementing it that i restrict the command to execute the @code{man [section] page} command.
@end quotation

So i decide to provide the same functionality but without restricting it to the manpage displaying, to expand it to execute any command you want in an toplevel terminal.

It result in a functionality to execute a command in a toplevel terminal, which can be resize, minimize, maximize and close.

After the execution of the command the toplevel terminal is yours and can continue to enter commands...


@display
@w{ }
@end display



I intend to implement launching of @code{registered offline HTML documentation} in a toplevel window,

@quotation

but i remark by implementing it that i restrict it to offline @strong{HTML} pages.
@end quotation

So i decide to provide the same functionality with registering any file you like.

The registered files are launched with the default program for this filetype.

After registering the files, you can easy launch it and access them all directly from @strong{it-edit}.


@display
@w{ }
@end display



I want to launch necessary @strong{GUI tools} directly from the editor.

So @strong{it-edit} permit to register the application you want to get direct access to it from your editor.

Like: A @strong{GUI} @code{diff tool}, A @strong{GUI} @code{debugger}, a smart @code{python interpreter}, a @code{calculator}, a @code{color picker}, a @code{dictionary}, and so soon...
@end quotation

