@anchor{it-edit actions}@anchor{8}
@chapter Actions


@quotation

@strong{Command execution}: use the menu item, the @strong{Cmd} button or the shortcut: @strong{Ctrl + e}.

@quotation

This will display a little toplevel in which you can enter a command.

Then press the @strong{Enter} key or the @strong{Apply} button to execute the command in a terminal include in a toplevel window (so you can resize, minimize, maximize and close the window).

After the execution from the command the toplevel terminal is yours so can continue to enter commands and use it.
@end quotation

@strong{Sidebar Terminals adding}: You can add some terminals, 2 per item, to the sidebar, reorder them, and remove it.

@quotation

Use the menu item or the shortcut @strong{Ctrl + Maj + T}.
@end quotation

@strong{Big terminal(s) switch}: You can switch between a very big terminal and a very big terminal divided into 4 terminals.

@quotation

Use the menu item or the shortcut @strong{Ctrl + Maj + B}.
@end quotation

@strong{File Handler}: use the menu item or the shortcut: @strong{Ctrl + H}.

@quotation

For using this features you must register files from the @strong{Files handler manager} tab interface reachable through the settings->Configure program menu item.

For registering a file you must give it a title which will appears as the button text in the @strong{File Handler} window and selecting the corresponding file.

Then when you press the button in the @strong{File Handler} window, the file will be launched with the default application for this filetype.

This features was thinking for fast access to offline HTML documentation but it's being expanded to any filetype, so you can consult pdf documentation too, but not only, this features can be use for any use you want.

The registered files can be removed from the @strong{File handler} list through the same interface with which you add it.
@end quotation

@strong{Application launcher}: use the menu item or the shortcut: @strong{Ctrl + A}.

@quotation

This will display an application chooser. By selecting an application you will launch it.
@end quotation
@end quotation

